36 std::string type2str(int type) {
37  std::string r;
38 
39  uchar depth = type & CV_MAT_DEPTH_MASK;
40  uchar chans = 1 + (type >> CV_CN_SHIFT);
41 
42  switch (depth) {
43  case CV_8U:
44  r = "8U";
45  break;
46  case CV_8S:
47  r = "8S";
48  break;
49  case CV_16U:
50  r = "16U";
51  break;
52  case CV_16S:
53  r = "16S";
54  break;
55  case CV_32S:
56  r = "32S";
57  break;
58  case CV_32F:
59  r = "32F";
60  break;
61  case CV_64F:
62  r = "64F";
63  break;
64  default:
65  r = "User";
66  break;
67  }
68 
69  r += "C";
70  r += (chans + '0');
71 
72  // USAGE
73  // std::string ty = type2str( H.type() );
74  // printf("Matrix: %s %dx%d \n", ty.c_str(), H.cols, H.rows );
75 
76  return r;
77 }

79 cv::Mat captureFrame(bool color, bool useCalibration, cv::VideoCapture capture) {
80  cv::Mat inFrame, outFrame;
81  capture >> inFrame;
82 
83  // Check if frame should be color or grayscale
84  if (color == false && useCalibration == false) {
85  cv::cvtColor(inFrame, outFrame, CV_RGB2GRAY); // grayscale
86  } else if (color == false && useCalibration == true) {
87  cv::Mat temp;
88  cv::undistort(inFrame, temp, cameraMatrix, distCoeffs);
89  cv::cvtColor(temp, outFrame, CV_RGB2GRAY); // grayscale
90  } else if (color == true && useCalibration == false) {
91  outFrame = inFrame;
92  } else {
93  cv::undistort(inFrame, outFrame, cameraMatrix, distCoeffs);
94  }
95 
96  return outFrame;
97 }

99 std::vector<cv::DMatch> knnMatchDescriptors(cv::Mat descriptors_object, cv::Mat descriptors_scene, float nnratio) {
100  cv::FlannBasedMatcher matcher;
101  std::vector<std::vector<cv::DMatch> > matches;
102 
103  // Match descriptors
104  matcher.knnMatch(descriptors_object, descriptors_scene, matches, 2);
105 
106  std::vector<cv::DMatch> good_matches;
107  good_matches.reserve(matches.size());
108 
109  for (size_t i = 0; i < matches.size(); ++i) {
110  if (matches[i].size() < 2)
111  continue;
112 
113  const cv::DMatch &m1 = matches[i][0];
114  const cv::DMatch &m2 = matches[i][1];
115 
116  if (m1.distance <= nnratio * m2.distance)
117  good_matches.push_back(m1);
118  }
119 
120  return good_matches;
121 }

147 std::vector<cv::DMatch> matchDescriptors(cv::Mat descriptors_object, cv::Mat descriptors_scene) {
148  // Good at filtering FLANN based match.
149  cv::FlannBasedMatcher matcher;
150  std::vector<cv::DMatch> matches;
151 
152  // Match descriptors
153  matcher.match(descriptors_object, descriptors_scene, matches);
154 
155  double max_dist = 0;
156  double min_dist = 100;
157 
158  // Compute the max and min distance of the matches in current videoFrame
159  for (int i = 0; i < descriptors_object.rows; i++) {
160  double dist = matches[i].distance;
161  if (dist < min_dist) min_dist = dist;
162  if (dist > max_dist) max_dist = dist;
163  }
164 
165  std::vector<cv::DMatch> good_matches;
166 
167  // Remove bad matches
168  double k = 2;
169  for (int i = 0; i < descriptors_object.rows; i++) {
170  if (matches[i].distance <= cv::max(k * min_dist, 0.02)) {
171  good_matches.push_back(matches[i]);
172  }
173  }
174 
175  return good_matches;
176 }

178 std::vector<cv::DMatch> bruteForce(cv::Mat descriptors_object, cv::Mat descriptors_scene, int normType) {
179  cv::BFMatcher matcher(normType);
180  std::vector<std::vector<cv::DMatch> > matches;
181  matcher.knnMatch(descriptors_object, descriptors_scene, matches, 2);
182 
183 // look whether the match is inside a defined area of the image
184 // only 25% of maximum of possible distance
185 // double tresholdDist = 0.25 * sqrt(double(object.size().height*object.size().height
186 // +object.size().width*object.size().width));
187 
188  std::vector<cv::DMatch> good_matches;
189  for (int i = 0; i < matches.size(); ++i) {
190  const float ratio = 0.9; // As in Lowe's paper; can be tuned
191  if (matches[i][0].distance < ratio * matches[i][1].distance) {
192  good_matches.push_back(matches[i][0]);
193  }
194  }
195 
196  return good_matches;
197 }

351 std::vector<cv::DMatch> symmetryTest(const std::vector<cv::DMatch> &matches1, const std::vector<cv::DMatch> &matches2) {
352  std::vector<cv::DMatch> symMatches;
353  for (std::vector<cv::DMatch>::const_iterator matchIterator1 = matches1.begin();
354  matchIterator1 != matches1.end(); ++matchIterator1) {
355  for (std::vector<cv::DMatch>::const_iterator matchIterator2 = matches2.begin();
356  matchIterator2 != matches2.end(); ++matchIterator2) {
357  if ((*matchIterator1).queryIdx == (*matchIterator2).trainIdx &&
358  (*matchIterator2).queryIdx == (*matchIterator1).trainIdx) {
359  symMatches.push_back(
360  cv::DMatch((*matchIterator1).queryIdx, (*matchIterator1).trainIdx, (*matchIterator1).distance));
361  break;
362  }
363  }
364  }
365  return symMatches;
366 }

368 CurrentMatch visualizeMatch(cv::Mat searchImage, cv::Mat objectImage, std::vector<cv::KeyPoint> keypointsObject,
369  std::vector<cv::KeyPoint> keypointsScene, std::vector<cv::DMatch> good_matches,
370  bool showKeypoints, int homographyType) {
371 
372  cv::Mat image_matches;
373 
374  if (showKeypoints) {
375  cv::drawKeypoints(searchImage, keypointsScene, image_matches, cv::Scalar::all(-1),
376  cv::DrawMatchesFlags::NOT_DRAW_SINGLE_POINTS);
377 // cv::drawMatches(objectImage, keypointsObject, searchImage, keypointsScene, good_matches, image_matches,
378 // cv::Scalar::all(-1), cv::Scalar::all(-1), std::vector<char>(),
379 // cv::DrawMatchesFlags::NOT_DRAW_SINGLE_POINTS);
380  } else {
381  image_matches = searchImage.clone();
382  }
383 
384  std::vector<cv::Point2f> obj;
385  std::vector<cv::Point2f> scene;
386 
387  for (size_t i = 0; i < good_matches.size(); i++) {
388  // Retrieve the keypoints from good matches
389  obj.push_back(keypointsObject[good_matches[i].queryIdx].pt);
390  scene.push_back(keypointsScene[good_matches[i].trainIdx].pt);
391  }
392 
393  // Perform Homography to find a perspective transformation between two planes.
394  cv::Mat H;
395  if (!obj.size() == 0 && !scene.size() == 0) {
396  H = cv::findHomography(obj, scene, homographyType); // CV_LMEDS // CV_RANSAC
397  }
398 
399  std::vector<cv::Point2f> objectCorners(4);
400 
401  // Put object corners in a vector
402  objectCorners[0] = cvPoint(0, 0); //Upper left corner
403  objectCorners[1] = cvPoint(objectImage.cols, 0); //Upper right corner
404  objectCorners[2] = cvPoint(objectImage.cols, objectImage.rows); //Lower right corner
405  objectCorners[3] = cvPoint(0, objectImage.rows); //Lower left corner
406 
407  std::vector<cv::Point2f> sceneCorners(4);
408 
409  // Find the object corners in the scene perspective
410  if (!H.rows == 0 && !H.cols == 0) {
411  cv::perspectiveTransform(objectCorners, sceneCorners, H);
412 
413  if (checkObjectInnerAngles(sceneCorners, 60, 120)) {
414  // Draw lines surrounding the object
415  cv::line(image_matches, sceneCorners[0], sceneCorners[1], cv::Scalar(0, 255, 0), 2); //TOP line
416  cv::line(image_matches, sceneCorners[1], sceneCorners[2], cv::Scalar(0, 255, 0), 2); //RIGHT line
417  cv::line(image_matches, sceneCorners[2], sceneCorners[3], cv::Scalar(0, 255, 0), 2); //BOTTOM line
418  cv::line(image_matches, sceneCorners[3], sceneCorners[0], cv::Scalar(0, 255, 0), 2); //LEFT line
419  // Draw diagonals
420  cv::line(image_matches, sceneCorners[0], sceneCorners[2], cv::Scalar(0, 255, 0), 1); //DIAGONAL 0-2
421  cv::line(image_matches, sceneCorners[1], sceneCorners[3], cv::Scalar(0, 255, 0), 1); //DIAGONAL 1-3
422 
423  // Center
424  cv::Point2f cen(0.0, 0.0);
425  if (intersection(sceneCorners[0], sceneCorners[2], sceneCorners[1], sceneCorners[3], cen)) {
426  cv::circle(image_matches, cen, 10, cv::Scalar(0, 0, 255), 2);
427  }
428  }
429  }
430 
431  // Draw circles in center pixel of the video stream
432  if (searchImage.rows > 60 && searchImage.cols > 60) {
433  cv::circle(image_matches, cv::Point(searchImage.cols / 2, searchImage.rows / 2), 5, CV_RGB(255, 0, 0));
434  cv::circle(image_matches, cv::Point(searchImage.cols / 2, searchImage.rows / 2), 10, CV_RGB(0, 255, 0));
435  cv::circle(image_matches, cv::Point(searchImage.cols / 2, searchImage.rows / 2), 15, CV_RGB(0, 0, 255));
436  }
437 
438  CurrentMatch cm;
439  cm.outFrame = image_matches;
440  cm.sceneCorners = sceneCorners;
441 
442  return cm;
443 }

445 bool intersection(cv::Point2f o1, cv::Point2f p1, cv::Point2f o2, cv::Point2f p2, cv::Point2f &r) {
446  // The lines are defined by (o1, p1) and (o2, p2).
447  cv::Point2f x = o2 - o1;
448  cv::Point2f d1 = p1 - o1;
449  cv::Point2f d2 = p2 - o2;
450 
451  float cross = d1.x * d2.y - d1.y * d2.x;
452  if (fabsf(cross) < /*EPS*/1e-8)
453  return false;
454 
455  double t1 = (x.x * d2.y - x.y * d2.x) / cross;
456  r = o1 + d1 * t1;
457  return true;
458 }

460 int innerAngle(cv::Point2f a, cv::Point2f b, cv::Point2f c) {
461  cv::Point2f ab(b.x - a.x, b.y - a.y);
462  cv::Point2f cb(b.x - c.x, b.y - c.y);
463 
464  double dot = (ab.x * cb.x + ab.y * cb.y); // dot product
465  double cross = (ab.x * cb.y - ab.y * cb.x); // cross product
466 
467  double alpha = atan2(cross, dot);
468 
469  int angle = (int) floor(alpha * 180. / PI + 0.5);
470  //alpha = alpha * 180 / PI;
471 
472  return abs(angle);
473 }

475 bool checkObjectInnerAngles(std::vector<cv::Point2f> scorner, int min, int max) {
476  bool out = false;
477  int c0 = innerAngle(scorner[3], scorner[0], scorner[1]);
478  int c1 = innerAngle(scorner[0], scorner[1], scorner[2]);
479  int c2 = innerAngle(scorner[1], scorner[2], scorner[3]);
480  int c3 = innerAngle(scorner[2], scorner[3], scorner[0]);
481 
482  if (c0 > min && c0 < max && c1 > min && c1 < max && c2 > min && c2 < max && c3 > min && c3 < max) out = true;
483 
484  return out;
485 }

499 // bbox
500 cv::Point2f getObjectCentroidBbox(std::vector<cv::Point2f> scene) {
501  cv::Point2f pmin(1000000, 1000000);
502  cv::Point2f pmax(0, 0);
503  for (size_t i = 0; i < scene.size(); i++) {
504  if (scene[i].x < pmin.x) pmin.x = scene[i].x;
505  if (scene[i].y < pmin.y) pmin.y = scene[i].y;
506  if (scene[i].x > pmax.x) pmax.x = scene[i].x;
507  if (scene[i].y > pmax.y) pmax.y = scene[i].y;
508  }
509  cv::Point2f cen((pmax.x - pmin.x) / 2, (pmax.y - pmin.y) / 2);
510  return cen;
511 }

535 double getObjectAngle(cv::Mat frame, std::vector<cv::Point2f> scorner) {
536 
537  double centerX = frame.cols / 2;
538  double diffX = centerX - scorner[1].x;
539  double x = (centerX - diffX) - scorner[0].x;
540 
541  double y = scorner[0].y - scorner[1].y;
542 
543  double angle = atan2(y, x) * 180 / PI;

560  ros::init(argc, argv, "object_detection");
561  ros::NodeHandle n;
562  ros::Publisher pub1 = n.advertise<geometry_msgs::Pose2D>("/object_detection/offset1", 1);
563  ros::Publisher pub2 = n.advertise<geometry_msgs::Pose2D>("/object_detection/offset2", 1);
564  ros::Rate loop_rate(loop_frequency);
565 
566  // Read the image we are looking for
567  object_image = cv::imread(argv[1], CV_LOAD_IMAGE_GRAYSCALE);
568  object_image2 = cv::imread(argv[2], CV_LOAD_IMAGE_GRAYSCALE);
569  if (!object_image.data || !object_image2.data) {
570  ROS_ERROR(" --(!) Error reading images");
571  return 0;
572  }
573  ROS_INFO("Loaded reference images:\n\t1: %s\n\t2: %s", argv[1], argv[2]);
574 
575  // Close if no camera could be opened
576  if (!capture.open(0)) {
577  ROS_ERROR(" --(!) Could not reach camera");
578  return 0;
579  }
580  // Set resolution
581  capture.set(CV_CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH, resWidth);
582  capture.set(CV_CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT, resHeight);
583  ROS_INFO("Camera resolution: width=%f, height=%f",
584  capture.get(CV_CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH), capture.get(CV_CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT));
585 
586  // Detect keypoints and compute keypoints and descriptors for the reference image
587  bool binary = false;
588  bool bruteforce = true;
589  cv::Ptr<cv::Feature2D> detector = SetKeyPointsDetector(DETECTOR_TYPE);
590  cv::Ptr<cv::Feature2D> extractor = SetDescriptorsExtractor(EXTRACTOR_TYPE, binary);
591 // cv::Ptr<cv::Feature2D> detector = getKeypoints(BRISK);
592 // cv::Ptr<cv::Feature2D> extractor = getDescriptors(BRISK, binary);
593  ROS_INFO("Binary matching: %d", binary);
594  ROS_INFO("Bruteforce matching: %d", bruteforce);
595 
596  detector->detect(object_image, ko, deso);
597  detector->detect(object_image2, ko2, deso2);
598  extractor->compute(object_image, ko, deso);
599  extractor->compute(object_image2, ko2, deso2);
600 
601  // Output the reference keypoints we are looking for
602  cv::drawKeypoints(object_image, ko, ref_keypoints1);
603  cv::drawKeypoints(object_image2, ko2, ref_keypoints2);
604  cv::imwrite(ref_path1, ref_keypoints1);
605  cv::imwrite(ref_path2, ref_keypoints2);
606  ROS_INFO("Reference keypoints written:\n\t1: %s\n\t2: %s", ref_path1.c_str(), ref_path2.c_str());
607 
608  // Window to show the frames in
609  cv::namedWindow(OPENCV_WINDOW, CV_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN);
610 
611  // Set up services
612  ros::ServiceServer service1 = n.advertiseService("setProcessRunning", setProcessRunningCallBack);
613  ros::ServiceServer service2 = n.advertiseService("getProcessRunning", getProcessRunningCallBack);
614 
615  cameraMatrix = getCameraMatrix(CALIBRATION_FILE);
616  distCoeffs = getDistortionCoeff(CALIBRATION_FILE);
617 
618  // Loop until program is stopped
619  ROS_INFO("Processing video stream at loop rate [Hz]: %f", loop_frequency);
620  int count = 0;
621  while (ros::ok()) {
622  // Capture video frame
623  videoFrame = captureFrame(false, false, capture);
624  if (videoFrame.empty()) break; // || cv::waitKey(30) >= 0
625  cv::waitKey(30);
626 
627  // Process frames
628  if (running) {
629  // Detect keypoints and descriptors
630  detector->detect(videoFrame, ks);
631  extractor->compute(videoFrame, ks, dess);
632 
633  // Match descriptors of reference and video frame
634  std::vector<cv::DMatch> good_matches, good_matches2;
635  if (!binary) {
636  if (bruteforce) {
637  good_matches = bruteForce(deso, dess, cv::NORM_L1);
638  good_matches2 = bruteForce(deso2, dess, cv::NORM_L1);
639  } else {
640  good_matches = knnMatchDescriptors(deso, dess, 0.9f);
641  good_matches2 = knnMatchDescriptors(deso2, dess, 0.9f);
642  }
643  } else {
644  if(bruteforce) {
645  good_matches = bruteForce(deso, dess, cv::NORM_HAMMING);
646  good_matches2 = bruteForce(deso2, dess, cv::NORM_HAMMING);
647  } else {
648  good_matches = knnMatchDescriptorsLSH(deso, dess, 0.9f);
649  good_matches2 = knnMatchDescriptorsLSH(deso2, dess, 0.9f);
650  }
651  }
652 
653  // Visualize matching
654  if ((!ko.size() == 0 && !ks.size() == 0) && good_matches.size() >= 0) {
655 
656  match1 = visualizeMatch(videoFrame, object_image, ko, ks, good_matches, true, CV_RANSAC);
657  match2 = visualizeMatch(match1.outFrame, object_image2, ko2, ks, good_matches2, false, CV_RANSAC);
658 
659  cv::imshow(OPENCV_WINDOW, match2.outFrame);
660  } else {
661  cv::imshow(OPENCV_WINDOW, videoFrame);
662  }
663  } else {
664  cv::imshow(OPENCV_WINDOW, videoFrame);
665  }
666 
667 
668  if (count == 40) {
669  // Do x, y, theta calculation
670  running = true;
671  //count = 0;
672  }
673 
674  // ROS
675  if (match2.sceneCorners.size() == 4 && checkObjectInnerAngles(match2.sceneCorners, 60, 120)) {
676  pose_msg.theta = getObjectAngle(videoFrame, match2.sceneCorners);
677  pose_msg.x = getXoffset(videoFrame, match2.sceneCorners);
678  pose_msg.y = getYoffset(videoFrame, match2.sceneCorners);
679  pub1.publish(pose_msg);
680  }
681  if (match1.sceneCorners.size() == 4 && checkObjectInnerAngles(match1.sceneCorners, 60, 120)) {
682  pose_msg.theta = getObjectAngle(videoFrame, match1.sceneCorners);
683  pose_msg.x = getXoffset(videoFrame, match1.sceneCorners);
684  pose_msg.y = getYoffset(videoFrame, match1.sceneCorners);
685  pub2.publish(pose_msg);
686  }
687  ros::spinOnce();
688  loop_rate.sleep();
689  ++count;
690  }
691  cv::destroyWindow(OPENCV_WINDOW);
692  ROS_INFO("Object detection shutting down");
693 
694  return 0;
695 }
